	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I decided to rewrite my cpu core, as my old one had a bug or two I just couldn't track down, and was too messy. I decided to use nestest to try out the new one, but have been unable to get any results. I set my program counter to 0xC000 and ran it. It eventually hit a unofficial opcode and exited. I expected to find results for the official opcodes, even though it did not completely finish. Instead, all I have are 00 at 2h and 3h. Is my core broken to the point that nestest can't even report problems?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


